<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Thinouia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thinouia trifoliata" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trifoliata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Thinouia trifoliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the 5-lobed floral disc, fruits with trichomes and basal petal appendages smaller than the petals, versus annular disc, glabrous fruits and marginal petal appendages larger than the petals.
</paragraph>
