<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Medeiros" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Thinouia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="cazumbensis" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cazumbensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">cazumbensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to Reserva Extrativista do 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cazumbá-Iracema">Cazumba-Iracema</normalizedToken>
, where the species was collected. In the 1980s, local rubber tappers and extractivists fought against the area becoming a rural settlement and on 19 September 2002 succeeded in getting the area designated as a conservation unit (
<bibRefCitation author="ICMBio" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" publicationUrl="https://www.icmbio.gov.br/portal/resex-do-cazumba-iracema" refId="B7" refString="ICMBio, 2007. Plano de Manejo da Reserva Extrativista do Cazumba-Iracema. Sena Madureira. https://www.icmbio.gov.br/portal/resex-do-cazumba-iracema" title="Plano de Manejo da Reserva Extrativista do Cazumba-Iracema. Sena Madureira." url="https://www.icmbio.gov.br/portal/resex-do-cazumba-iracema" year="2007">ICMBio 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Situated in the State of Acre between the municipalities of Sena Madureira and Manoel Urbano, the Reserva Extrativista do 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cazumbá-Iracema">Cazumba-Iracema</normalizedToken>
covers an area of 750,794.70 hectares of the Western Amazon Corridor, one of the seven major ecological corridors proposed for Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Ricardo, MM" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B15" refString="Ricardo, MM, Lima, RX, 2004. Corredores ecologicos e suas politicas de implementacao. Congresso Brasileiro de Unidades de Conservacao, 4., Anais (Vol. 2). Seminarios. FBPN e Rede Nacional Pro-Unidades de Conservacao, Curitiba." title="Corredores ecologicos e suas politicas de implementacao. Congresso Brasileiro de Unidades de Conservacao, 4., Anais (Vol. 2). Seminarios. FBPN e Rede Nacional Pro-Unidades de Conservacao, Curitiba." year="2004">Ricardo and Lima 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
The species is only known from one locality in Acre and is categorised as Data Deficient (DD) according to 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B8" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Standards and Petitions Committee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Standards and Petitions Committee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. Further field studies are needed to evaluate its conservation status more accurately.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
